 framework, the first peak results\nfrom a post-shock cooling phase for an extended progenitor, and the luminous\nmain peak is due to a large nickel production. These characteristics are\ncompatible with the pair-instability SN scenario. We note, however, that a\nsignificant contribution of interaction with circumstellar material cannot be\nruled out.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Jun 2022 16:16:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Oct 2022 13:47:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-27"}
