nventional computationally expensive method\nthat iteratively solves the inverse QoS problem. We further develop lower and\nupper bounds on the performance of this scaling scheme. Simulation results show\nthat the proposed algorithms offer near-optimal performance with substantially\nlower computational complexity than the state-of-the-art algorithms for\nlarge-scale systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Jun 2022 22:42:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 14 Apr 2023 02:05:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-17"}
